Use Gist #   Copy script tag from up right of the Gist. Paste script tag in the body.  Use prism.js #   prism.js is a syntax highlighter written in js. Add the following code in the head.  &lt;link href=&#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.17.1/themes/prism-twilight.min.css&#39; rel=&#39;stylesheet&#39;/&gt; &lt;link href=&#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.17.1/plugins/line-numbers/prism-line-numbers.min.css&#39; rel=&#39;stylesheet&#39;/&gt;  Additionally, insert following code in the body.  &lt;script src=&#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.17.1/prism.min.js&#39;/&gt; &lt;script src=&#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.17.1/plugins/autoloader/prism-autoloader.min.js&#39;/&gt; &lt;script src=&#39;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.17.1/plugins/line-numbers/prism-line-numbers.min.js&#39;/&gt;  Example:  &lt;pre class=&#34;line-numbers&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-c&#34;&gt;#include &amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt; int main(){ printf(&#34;Hello, World!\n&#34;); }&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt; About #   It is easy to add MathJax to your web site. All you have to do is add following script tag in the body tag.  &lt;script src=&#34;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.5/latest.js?config=TeX-MML-AM_CHTML&#34; async&gt;&lt;/script&gt; Usage #   General:  \[a^2 + b^2 = c^2\] % or  \begin{align} 1 &amp;= e^{i\theta}e^{-i\theta}\\ &amp;= \left(\cos{\theta}+i\sin{\theta}\right) \left(\cos{\theta}-i\sin{\theta}\right)\\ &amp;= \sin^2{\theta}+\cos^2{\theta} \end{align}   Inline: \(y = \alpha x + \beta\)
  If you need formula numbers add this script in the body tag.
  &lt;script type=&#34;text/x-mathjax-config&#34;&gt; MathJax.Hub.Config({ TeX: { equationNumbers: { autoNumber: &#34;all&#34; } } }); &lt;/script&gt;
